---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About • Historical Translation Project™" description="Our mission: translate global historical remedies into modern evidence-forward education and formulas.">
  
  <section class="container-xl section">
    <div class="kicker">About</div>
    <h1 class="h2 mt-2">A research‑first initiative bridging history and modern evidence.</h1>
    <p class="sub mt-3">
      Historical Translation Project™ researches ancient and medieval preventive frameworks across cultures—and responsibly translates what holds up into modern, evidence‑forward educational dossiers and thoughtfully designed botanical formulas.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <h2 class="h3">Our mission</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted leading-relaxed">
          To continue researching ancient remedies throughout the globe and throughout history, then bring those insights together with modern scientific standards—clearly, conservatively, and without hype.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We focus on education first: citations, context, and safety framing. Our formulations follow the same philosophy—designed for everyday routine support using compliant structure/function language. This is not medical advice.
        </p>

        <h2 class="h3 mt-10">What makes our work different</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-muted">
          <li><b>Historically anchored:</b> grounded in primary preventive models (starting with Rambam/Maimonides as our inaugural project).</li>
          <li><b>Evidence‑forward:</b> we prioritize reputable modern sources (NIH ODS, NCCIH, WHO/EMA monographs, PubMed-indexed reviews).</li>
          <li><b>Compliance‑minded:</b> conservative structure/function language—no disease claims, no treatment promises.</li>
          <li><b>Quality‑oriented:</b> identity verification and contaminant screening are treated as baseline expectations.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-5 card p-6">
        <div class="kicker">Principles</div>
        <h3 class="mt-2 font-serif text-2xl text-navy">Clarity over hype.</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We aim to make historical material readable and scientifically responsible—so consumers can learn, not be sold.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/evidence">Evidence & Safety</a>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Educational content only; not medical advice. Supplements are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
